cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about domain adaptation for neural machine translation, which is a topic in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a method that involves modeling domain-specific and domain-independent information, which is related to machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions using a discriminator and adversarial training, which are techniques commonly used in computer vision (CV) and neural networks (NE), respectively, making cs.CV and cs.NE possible categories as well.
